		<description>The Fenghuang is a legendary bird in East Asian mythologies symbolyzing high virtue and grace. The fenghuang also symbolizes the union of yin and yang, and it is believed that the bird only appears in areas or places that are blessed with utmost peace and prosperity or happiness. Traditionally described as a composite of many birds it is also often called a "Chinese Phoenix", although similarities with the western Phoenix are superficial.\n\nFenghuangs aren't naturally occurring creatures, and were created as part of the Hecate Project, a bio-engineering program that applied mechanite replicators to already existing animals to mutate them into "magical" creatures.\n\nSpecial Abilities: Tamed Fenghuangs radiate an aura of peace and tranquility, elevating the spirits of those nearby.</description>
